                                                          </div>
                                                                                            <p style="margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><a href="https://jpaden4.wixsite.com/jeremypadenpoet"><strong>Jeremy Paden</strong>&nbsp;</a>was born in Milan, Italy, in 1974 and is professor of Latin American literature at Transylvania University in Lexington, Kentucky, and on faculty at Spalding University’s low-residency MFA. He is a scholar, poet, and literary translator writing in both English and Spanish. His Spanish-language translation of Ada Limón’s&nbsp;<em>The Hurting Kind</em>&nbsp;has just been published in Spain with Valparaíso Ediciones.</p>

